The chief justice was elected President of the Conference of Constitutional Jurisdictions of Africa. JOHANNESBURG/CAPE TOWN - President Jacob Zuma has congratulated Chief Justice Mogoeng Mogoeng on his election as president of the Conference of Constitutional Jurisdictions of Africa.Zuma has wished Mogoeng well as he takes on new responsibilities.The president has also welcomed the election at a time where the continent is gearing up to mark Africa Month.Mogoeng says judges must be men and women of integrity.He says this plays a crucial role in eradicating corruption.Mogoeng, however, stresses this can only be achieved if judges are not corrupt.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)